08/08/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police arrested 27 suspected drug dealers during a two-day operation in Republika Srpska (RS), media reported on Friday (August 6th). Banja Luka Public Security Centre Deputy Director Zeljko Domazet said the police seized drugs, weapons and grenades during searches in 30 sites in RS. (RTRS, BHRT, Radio Free Europe - 06/08/10) 
